Others: England defeated Bosnia and Herzegovina 3-0 in a pre-Euro 2024 friendly match.
Cole Palmer scored a penalty to give England the lead, and Trent Alexander-Arnold and Harry Kane added late goals.
Gareth Southgate used several players out of position, particularly at full-back, as England struggled to find their rhythm in the first half.
Eberechi Eze and Cole Palmer were standout performers for England, demonstrating a lack of fear and a willingness to make things happen.
The St James' Park crowd in Newcastle, England, was enthusiastic but the match did not live up to their expectations, with a distinct lack of incisiveness from England.
